<h1>Problem 2236 - 2021 Mediterranean MO, P3 of 4, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be an equiangular triangle with circumcircle \(\omega\). Let point \(F\in AB\) and point \(E\in AC\) so that \(\angle ABE+\angle ACF=60^{\circ}\). The circumcircle of triangle \(AFE\) intersects the circle \(\omega\) in the point \(D\). The halflines \(DE\) and \(DF\) intersect the line through \(B\) and \(C\) in the points \(X\) and \(Y\). Prove that the incenter of the triangle \(DXY\) is independent of the choice of \(E\) and \(F\).</p>
